name: nedryland
description: Nedryland is a collection of utilities and a build system for declaring, building and deploying microservice solutions.

name: BloggingSystem_Microservice
description: This repository contains a microservice architecture for a blogging system, featuring Posting, Commenting, Moderation, and Data Storage Query services. Built with TypeScript, Node.js, Express.js, RabbitMQ, React, and Tailwind CSS. Includes setup instructions for RabbitMQ using Docker.

name: java-microservices
description: Implemented advanced system design principles, such as API Gateway, Service Discovery, Distributed Tracing, Circuit Breaking, Monitoring, and Logging, to optimize scalability, reliability, and performance of an application.

name: GOLocator
description: System for managing client location made with two microservices

name: MicroService_Simple_Ecommerce
description: This repository is a learning project for microservices architecture and message brokering systems. It includes three services: user, product, and order management. Built with RabbitMQ, Kubernetes, Docker, TypeScript, Node.js, Express.js, and React.

name: jobboard-backend
description: Job Board system with Spring Microservices, RabbitMQ, Jenkins, Docker and Kubernetes.

name: online-marketplace-system
description: The Online Marketplace Backend System is designed to power a dynamic online marketplace similar to e-Bay, enabling seamless buying and selling experiences for users. With robust features and secure transaction handling, the APIs facilitate the listing, searching, and purchasing of both new and used products within specified price ranges.

name: ESDG6
description: ESD project. Doctor Appointment/Consultation booking system using microservice architecture constructed and deployed via Docker

name: services-aws
description: Microservices system for seamless file upload to Amazon S3 and automatic transfer to DynamoDB using AWS Lambda.
